&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://dinersclubofferstool.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/APAC-SYDNEY-THE-BRIDGE-ROOM-OFFER-LOGO.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-8040&quot; src=&quot;http://dinersclubofferstool.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/APAC-SYDNEY-THE-BRIDGE-ROOM-OFFER-LOGO.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;APAC- SYDNEY- THE BRIDGE ROOM- OFFER- LOGO&quot; width=&quot;75&quot; height=&quot;75&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;Located just steps from Circular Quay and right in the heart of Sydney, The Bridge Room dazzles with refined elegance. The intimate Scandinavian-style dining room is decorated with parquet floors, light oak tables, banquette seating and custom touches everywhere, including ceramics designed by Chef Lusted himself.&nbsp; Ross Lusted&rsquo;s cuisine has been influenced by his travels in Asia with many of his dishes ash-grilled or slow smoked over binchotan charcoal on his Robata grill. His unique flavour pairings and technique earned him Good Food Guide&rsquo;s &ldquo;Chef of the Year,&rdquo; The Australian&rsquo;s &ldquo;Hottest Chef,&rdquo; and Four Chef&rsquo;s Hats Gault Millau Guide 2014. The menu constantly evolves according to the seasons and you will experience dishes such as wild caught raw snapper with preserved watermelon peel, salted lemon and red grapefruit or main courses such Ash-grilled duck, blueberries, caramelized pear puree, aged vinegar and mulberry powder; or crisp skinned Murray cod, black vinegar and Teochew sauce with cloud ear mushrooms and new season ginger. Dessert at The Bridge Room is a must-have so try Lusted&rsquo;s acclaimed whipped black sesame served with toasted sesame powder, melon, puffed rice and coconut sugar. Smart casual attire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please book online at The Bridge Room &nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bridgeroom.com.au/reservations&quot;&gt;website&lt;/a&gt;, &nbsp;by phone at +61-2-9247-7000 or email&nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:reservations@thebridgeroom.com.au&quot;&gt;reservations@thebridgeroom.com.au&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mention Diners Club International Privileges Dining Collection to receive your special benefit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide your name, date you would like to dine, number of guests, preferred time, cell phone or local (hotel) phone number and email address&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Bridge Room does not require a credit card at the time of booking to hold your reservation for parties of 6 or less guests. For parties of 10 guests or more, a deposit will be taken at the time of booking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cancellation Policy: If not cancelled 48 hours prior to the dining date or in the event of a no show, the entire deposit amount will be forfeited with no refund&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconfirmation Policy: The restaurant will contact the guest 24-48 hours prior to your dining date to reconfirm. If not reconfirmed your reservation may be given away if need arises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TERMS &amp;amp; CONDITIONS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow booking instructions to ensure receiving your Privileges Dining Collection amenity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based on availability at the time of booking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A main course must be purchased to receive your dining benefit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your Privileges Dining Collection benefit may not be combined with other offers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fulfillment of the offer is the sole responsibility of the participating restaurant merchant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Restaurant participation and benefits are subject to change or cancellation without notice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

